Customs officials of SARS and the SAPS were doing routine inspections on vehicles coming into South Africa, when they discovered the drugs valued at over R32 million at about 08:00. The drugs were covered with pieces of charcoal. Over R30 000 in cash was also seized. ALSO READ: The magic number: Over 800 suspects arrested in one week in Mpumalanga  The suspect is expected to appear in the Komatipoort Magistrate’s Court tomorrow on charges of the possession of drugs. The full story will be in this week’s Lowvelder.